{"title":"Mod0 Fundamentos Fisiologicos iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/Mod0 Fundamentos Fisiologicos iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"MÓDULO 0: FUNDAMENTOS\\NFISIOLÓGICOS DE MECÁNICA\\NRESPIRATORIA","guid":"efsu4JmacEkwjGXoXKMrTQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"CONCEPTOS\\NFUNDAMENTALES","guid":"IFP2F6dqNs3LINsxb7ZoSw","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Ecuación de\\Nmovimiento del\\Nsistema respiratorio","guid":"oT2BZOtX8krQ8usmP6pcDg","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"Paw = Pelástica + Presidiva + PEEP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"Paw = (Vt/Crs) + (Raw × Flujo) + PEEP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"2","text":"BASE de toda la ventilación mecánica → entender esta ecuación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"Respiración\\Nespontánea vs VM","guid":"5LdDVL1mYERGWEmJ0si2wQ","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"Espontánea → presión NEGATIVA (contracción diafragma)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"VM → presión POSITIVA (ventilador empuja aire)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"6","text":"Mismo resultado: flujo + intercambio gaseoso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"6","text":"DIFERENTE hemodinámica → VM ↓ retorno venoso por ↑ presión intratorácica","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"0","text":"COMPLIANCE\\N(DISTENSIBILIDAD)","guid":"9HTT2Glyt_4_cMJh_VcNIQ","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"Definición\\Nbásica","guid":"waFnbc3T_DFzuphJuqa8qA","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"Cambio de volumen por unidad de cambio de presión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"12","text":"C = ΔV / ΔP (mL/cmH2O)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"12","text":"ALTA compliance → pulmón fácil de inflar (ej: enfisema)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"12","text":"BAJA compliance → pulmón rígido (ej: SDRA, fibrosis, EPA)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"11","text":"Compliance\\NESTÁTICA\\N(Cest)","guid":"Kq9YHbF5vpCgBYFJDfmQng","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"Medida SIN flujo → pausa inspiratoria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"Cest = Vt / (Pplat - PEEP total)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"17","text":"Normal en VM: 50-100 mL/cmH2O","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"17","text":"< 25 mL/cmH2O → trabajo respiratorio MUY alto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"17","text":"Refleja SOLO propiedades elásticas del pulmón + pared torácica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"11","text":"Compliance\\NDINÁMICA\\N(Cdyn)","guid":"8iqESLoGnCf3c5-agoaVVg","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"Medida CON flujo presente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"Cdyn = Vt / (PIP - PEEP)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"23","text":"Incluye componente resistivo → siempre < Cest","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"23","text":"Si Cdyn cae pero Cest estable → problema RESISTIVO (secreciones, broncoespasmo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"23","text":"Si AMBAS caen → problema ELÁSTICO (atelectasia, edema, neumotórax)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"11","text":"Compliance\\Ndel sistema\\Nrespiratorio","guid":"UmZ56MFvOAPwHWDC6zdHQQ","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"Crs = Cpulmonar + Cpared torácica (en serie)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"1/Crs = 1/CL + 1/Ccw","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"CL depende de → surfactante, tensión superficial, elastina/colágena","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"29","text":"Ccw depende de → rigidez costal, cifosis, obesidad, ascitis","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"11","text":"IMPORTANCIA\\NCLÍNICA EN UPC","guid":"uwQ6GvF-b_yp96qcq57YXg","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"Cest baja → alarma de deterioro pulmonar (SDRA progresando, atelectasia, EPA)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"Monitorizar tendencia → más útil que valor aislado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"34","text":"Guía para titular PEEP → mejor compliance = mejor reclutamiento","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"0","text":"RESISTENCIA\\NDE VÍA AÉREA\\N(Raw)","guid":"upNyrHwB4JlWi2Pj4cSioQ","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"Definición\\Nbásica","guid":"SKL7QlbtrMIGvlHune32Yw","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"Oposición al flujo de gas por las vías aéreas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"Raw = (PIP - Pplat) / Flujo (cmH2O/L/s)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"39","text":"Normal sin intubación: 0.6-2.4 cmH2O/L/s","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"39","text":"Con TET: 5-10 cmH2O/L/s (↑ al ↓ diámetro TET)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"38","text":"Determinantes\\Nde resistencia","guid":"l09h5XlbieO3XlcRvagTWQ","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"Ley de Poiseuille → R proporcional a 1/radio⁴","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"Radio del tubo → FACTOR MÁS IMPORTANTE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"44","text":"TET 7.0 vs 8.0 → diferencia significativa en Raw","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"44","text":"Longitud del tubo (↑ largo = ↑ resistencia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"44","text":"Viscosidad y densidad del gas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"44","text":"Tipo de flujo → laminar vs turbulento","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"38","text":"Causas de ↑ resistencia en UPC","guid":"","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"Broncoespasmo → respuesta inmediata a broncodilatadores","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"51","text":"Secreciones en vía aérea o TET → aspiración","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"51","text":"Mordedura del TET → cánula de Guedel","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"51","text":"Acodamiento del TET o circuito","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"51","text":"Edema de mucosa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"57","parent":"38","text":"Patrón en ondas del ventilador","guid":"","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"PIP ↑ con Pplat normal → problema RESISTIVO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"PIP ↑ con Pplat ↑ → problema de COMPLIANCE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"57","text":"CLAVE DIAGNÓSTICA en alarma de presión alta","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"0","text":"CONSTANTE\\NDE TIEMPO\\N(τ)","guid":"qiI9ArMJIPjFC2uYLaWDXg","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"Definición","guid":"","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"τ = Compliance × Resistencia (segundos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"62","text":"Tiempo para que el 63% del volumen sea entregado o exhalado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"62","text":"3τ → 95% del volumen","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"62","text":"5τ → 99% del volumen (equilibrio completo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"61","text":"Importancia clínica PRÁCTICA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"τ CORTA (pulmón rígido, baja compliance)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"Ej: SDRA, fibrosis → τ ~0.2-0.3s","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"Tolera FR altas sin atrapamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"68","text":"Patrón: respiración rápida y superficial","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"67","text":"τ LARGA (alta resistencia)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"Ej: EPOC, asma → τ ~0.5-1.0s o más","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"Necesita tiempo espiratorio prolongado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"RIESGO de auto-PEEP si Te insuficiente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"72","text":"Patrón: respiración lenta y profunda","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"77","parent":"61","text":"Auto-PEEP (PEEP intrínseco)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"78","parent":"77","text":"Gas atrapado al final de espiración","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"77","text":"Causas → τ larga + Te corto + FR alta + Vt alto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"77","text":"Detección → pausa espiratoria (flujo no llega a cero)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"77","text":"Consecuencias → sobredistensión, ↓ retorno venoso, ↑ trabajo trigger","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"77","text":"EN PERSONA MAYOR → especialmente problemático por ↑ compliance pulmonar + cierre precoz vía aérea","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"0","text":"INTERCAMBIO\\NGASEOSO","guid":"afSfUHCmxJrD99ZtrFUreg","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"V/Q (Ventilación/Perfusión)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"Relación V/Q normal ~0.8 (4L ventilación / 5L perfusión)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"84","text":"V/Q = 0 → SHUNT (perfusión sin ventilación)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"Alvéolo colapsado o lleno de líquido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"NO responde a ↑ FiO2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"86","text":"Ej: atelectasia, SDRA, neumonía consolidada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"90","parent":"84","text":"V/Q = infinito → ESPACIO MUERTO (ventilación sin perfusión)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"91","parent":"90","text":"Alvéolo ventilado pero no perfundido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"90","text":"Ej: TEP, bajo gasto cardíaco, sobredistensión por PEEP excesivo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"84","text":"V/Q bajo (no cero) → DESIGUALDAD V/Q","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Causa MÁS COMÚN de hipoxemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"SÍ responde a ↑ FiO2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"93","text":"Ej: neumonía parcial, atelectasias parciales, broncoespasmo","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"83","text":"Espacio muerto","guid":"","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"Anatómico: ~150 mL (vía aérea de conducción, no participa en intercambio)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"Alveolar: alvéolos ventilados pero mal perfundidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"97","text":"Fisiológico = anatómico + alveolar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"97","text":"Vd/Vt normal: 0.25-0.35","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"97","text":"Vd/Vt > 0.6 → weaning difícil, ventilación ineficiente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"97","text":"EN PERSONA MAYOR → Vd/Vt ↑ (235 mL vs 150 mL en jóvenes según Tenney & Miller)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"83","text":"Difusión","guid":"","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"Ley de Fick → área × gradiente × solubilidad / grosor membrana","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"CO2 difunde 20× más rápido que O2 → la hipercapnia NO es problema de difusión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"104","text":"Superficie de intercambio ↓ con edad: 75 m² (30 años) → 60 m² (70 años)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"104","text":"DLCO ↓ con edad → relevante en enfermedad intersticial","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"0","text":"TRABAJO\\NRESPIRATORIO\\N(WOB)","guid":"ExNEnr-IgtzCWgKB8A-pHw","children":[{"id":"110","parent":"109","text":"Definición","guid":"","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"Energía requerida para mover gas dentro y fuera del pulmón","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"110","text":"WOB = Presión × Volumen (Joules)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"110","text":"Normal: 0.3-0.7 J/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"110","text":"> 1.5 J/L → fatiga probable","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"109","text":"Componentes del WOB","guid":"","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"Elástico → vencer retroceso pulmonar + pared torácica (~65%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"Resistivo → vencer fricción vía aérea (~28%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"115","text":"Inercial → despreciable en respiración normal (~7%)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"109","text":"Fatiga muscular respiratoria","guid":"","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"Diafragma = músculo respiratorio PRINCIPAL (70% del WOB)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"Fatiga cuando demanda > 40% de presión inspiratoria máxima (PImax)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"Signos clínicos → taquipnea, respiración paradójica, uso de accesorios","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"119","text":"IRREVERSIBLE sin reposo → indicación de VM como soporte","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"124","parent":"109","text":"Presión-tiempo producto (PTP)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"Integra presión × tiempo (cmH2O × s)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"124","text":"Mejor predictor de consumo O2 muscular que WOB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"124","text":"Normal: 50-150 cmH2O × s/min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"124","text":"> 200 → fatiga inminente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"129","parent":"109","text":"RELEVANCIA EN UPC","guid":"","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"Monitorizar WOB → guía para nivel de soporte ventilatorio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"Soporte excesivo → VIDD (atrofia diafragma por desuso)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"Soporte insuficiente → fatiga → fracaso de weaning","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"129","text":"EQUILIBRIO CRÍTICO → especialmente en persona mayor con sarcopenia","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"134","parent":"0","text":"CAMBIOS DEL\\NENVEJECIMIENTO\\NEN SISTEMA\\NRESPIRATORIO","guid":"50Qu1Cldp840gJjDZ8vPpw","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"Pared torácica y estructura","guid":"","children":[{"id":"136","parent":"135","text":"Calcificación articulaciones costocondrales → ↓ compliance pared torácica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"135","text":"Cifosis dorsal por osteoporosis → diafragma en desventaja mecánica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"135","text":"↓ Compliance pared torácica 30% a los 70 años (Mittman 1965)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"135","text":"Aplanamiento diafragmático → menor excursión","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"140","parent":"134","text":"Parénquima pulmonar","guid":"","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"Pérdida tejido de soporte → ENFISEMA SENIL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"140","text":"Dilatación homogénea de espacios aéreos (no destrucción como EPOC)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"140","text":"↑ Compliance pulmonar (~3 veces entre 50 y 80 años)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"140","text":"PERO ↓ retroceso elástico → cierre precoz de vía aérea pequeña","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"140","text":"Capacidad de cierre > CRF supina a los ~44 años → atelectasias basales","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"134","text":"Volúmenes pulmonares","guid":"","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"CPT → sin cambio significativo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"146","text":"VR → AUMENTA (atrapamiento por cierre precoz)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"146","text":"CRF → aumenta levemente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"146","text":"CV → DISMINUYE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"146","text":"VEF1 → cae ~30 mL/año, acelera después de 70 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"146","text":"Relación VEF1/CVF → disminuye con edad (no confundir con EPOC)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"134","text":"Musculatura respiratoria","guid":"","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"↓ Masa y fuerza diafragmática (sarcopenia respiratoria)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"PImax ↓ con edad → menor reserva ante ↑ demanda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"↓ Fuerza tos → clearance de secreciones comprometido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"153","text":"Hombres pierden más fuerza que mujeres","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"158","parent":"134","text":"Intercambio gaseoso","guid":"","children":[{"id":"159","parent":"158","text":"↓ Superficie alveolar: 75 m² → 60 m² (30-70 años)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"158","text":"↑ Espacio muerto alveolar → ventilación menos eficiente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"158","text":"↑ Desigualdad V/Q (zonas basales hipoperfundidas/hipoventiladas)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"158","text":"PaO2 esperada ↓ con edad: PaO2 ≈ 100 - (edad/3) mmHg (aproximación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"158","text":"PaCO2 → sin cambio significativo (compensado por ↑ ventilación minuto)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"158","text":"↓ DLCO → declina linealmente, más rápido en hombres","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"134","text":"Respuestas ventilatorias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"↓ Respuesta a HIPOXIA ~50% (Kronenberg 1973)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"165","text":"↓ Respuesta a HIPERCAPNIA ~40%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"165","text":"↓ Sensación de DISNEA → presentación TARDÍA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"165","text":"CONSECUENCIA CLÍNICA → llegan más graves, desaturan sin quejarse","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"165","text":"Mayor vulnerabilidad a falla ventilatoria en estados de alta demanda (neumonía, IC, sepsis)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"171","parent":"134","text":"Inmunidad pulmonar","guid":"","children":[{"id":"172","parent":"171","text":"↓ Clearance mucociliar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"171","text":"↓ IgA secretora","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"171","text":"Inmunosenescencia → mayor susceptibilidad infecciones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"171","text":"↓ Respuesta a vacunas (relevante en prevención)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"134","text":"IMPLICANCIAS PARA VM EN PERSONA MAYOR","guid":"","children":[{"id":"177","parent":"176","text":"Desaturación rápida en apnea → CRF baja + ↑ consumo O2/CRF","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"176","text":"Preoxigenación PROLONGADA obligatoria antes de IOT","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"176","text":"Vt 6-8 mL/kg peso IDEAL (no real) → evitar sobredistensión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"176","text":"PEEP individualizado → mayor tendencia a colapso basal pero ↑ compliance pulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"176","text":"Cuidado con auto-PEEP → compliance pulmonar alta + cierre precoz","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"176","text":"Weaning MÁS DIFÍCIL → sarcopenia + ↑ Vd/Vt + ↓ reserva muscular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"176","text":"Metas oxigenación PERMISIVAS → PaO2 60-70, SpO2 92-96% (no perseguir PaO2 >90)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"176","text":"Mayor riesgo VILI → barrera endotelial deteriorada con edad","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"185","parent":"0","text":"GASOMETRÍA ARTERIAL:\\NINTERPRETACIÓN SISTEMÁTICA","guid":"mBX3sT3AOwlXoKxzg1bx4Q","children":[{"id":"186","parent":"185","text":"Valores normales (ajustados a persona mayor)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"pH: 7.35-7.45","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"PaCO2: 35-45 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"186","text":"HCO3: 22-26 mEq/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"186","text":"PaO2: ajustar por edad → ~70-80 mmHg a los 70 años es NORMAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"186","text":"Lactato: <2 mmol/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"186","text":"BE: -2 a +2","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"193","parent":"185","text":"Método sistemático de interpretación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"PASO 1 → pH: ¿acidemia (<7.35) o alcalemia (>7.45)?","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"PASO 2 → Trastorno primario: ¿PaCO2 o HCO3 explican el pH?","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"193","text":"PASO 3 → Compensación: ¿es adecuada? (reglas de Winter, fórmulas)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"193","text":"PASO 4 → Anión gap: Na - (Cl + HCO3) → normal 8-12 mEq/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"193","text":"PASO 5 → Delta-delta: ΔAG/ΔHCO3 → trastornos mixtos ocultos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"193","text":"PASO 6 → Contexto clínico SIEMPRE → la gasometría no diagnostica sola","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"200","parent":"185","text":"Trastornos ácido-base FRECUENTES en UPC geriátrica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"201","parent":"200","text":"Acidosis respiratoria → hipoventilación (EPOC, sedación excesiva, fatiga)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"200","text":"Alcalosis respiratoria → hiperventilación (dolor, ansiedad, sepsis precoz)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"200","text":"Acidosis metabólica AG elevado → lactato (shock), cetoacidosis, uremia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"200","text":"Acidosis metabólica AG normal → diarrea, acidosis tubular, dilucional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"200","text":"Alcalosis metabólica → vómitos, diuréticos, contracción de volumen","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"200","text":"TRASTORNOS MIXTOS → la regla en pacientes complejos de UCI","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"207","parent":"185","text":"PaO2/FiO2 (PAFI)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"208","parent":"207","text":"Índice de oxigenación más usado en UCI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"207","text":"Normal: >400","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"207","text":"SDRA leve: 200-300","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"207","text":"SDRA moderado: 100-200","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"207","text":"SDRA severo: <100","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"207","text":"Limitación → influenciado por PEEP, FiO2 alta, posición","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"214","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"215","parent":"214","text":"Compliance estática es el PRIMER parámetro a revisar ante alarma de presión alta → si Pplat sube = problema elástico, si solo PIP sube = problema resistivo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"214","text":"En persona mayor: la compliance pulmonar está AUMENTADA pero la de pared torácica DISMINUIDA → efecto neto variable, individualizar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"214","text":"τ larga + persona mayor con EPOC → programar Te >3τ para evitar auto-PEEP catastrófico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"214","text":"PaO2 de 70 mmHg en un paciente de 75 años puede ser NORMAL → no escalar FiO2 innecesariamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"219","parent":"214","text":"Desaturación en apnea es 2-3× más rápida en >70 años → preoxigenar con CNAF o VMNI antes de IOT","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"220","parent":"214","text":"La fatiga diafragmática NO se revierte sin reposo muscular → si hay signos, intubar ANTES del colapso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"221","parent":"214","text":"WOB tiene zona óptima: muy poco soporte → fatiga; mucho soporte → atrofia (VIDD) → el balance es CRÍTICO en AM con sarcopenia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"214","text":"Gasometría arterial en persona mayor → SIEMPRE ajustar PaO2 esperada por edad antes de decidir oxigenoterapia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"214","text":"Delta-delta es la herramienta más subestimada en UCI → revela trastornos mixtos ocultos que cambian el manejo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"214","text":"Espacio muerto ↑ en persona mayor → para el mismo Vt, menos ventilación alveolar efectiva → considerar al programar FR","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"225","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIÉN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"226","parent":"225","text":"→ Monitoreo VM / VILI / P-SILI (Módulo 4)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"225","text":"→ Hipercapnia en VM (Módulo 1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"225","text":"→ Ondas del ventilador Chatburn (Módulo 3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"225","text":"→ Delta PCO2 (Módulo 0)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"230","parent":"225","text":"→ Weaning y liberación VM (Módulo 8)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"231","parent":"225","text":"→ Modos ventilatorios y programación (Módulo 3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"225","text":"→ Monitoreo VM (Módulo 4)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"225","text":"→ Hipercapnia VM (Módulo 1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"225","text":"→ Ondas ventilador (Módulo 3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"235","parent":"225","text":"→ Delta PCO2 (Módulo 0)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"236","parent":"225","text":"→ Weaning VM (Módulo 8)","guid":"x-TqEIWKg10hZYK4-r_Q-g","children":[]}]},{"id":"237","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"238","parent":"237","text":"1. Sharma G, Goodwin J. Effect of aging on respiratory system physiology and immunology. Clin Interv Aging. 2006;1(3):253-60.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"239","parent":"237","text":"2. Sprung J, Gajic O, Warner DO. Age related alterations in respiratory function. Br J Anaesth. 2006;97(1):99-109.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"237","text":"3. Hess DR. Respiratory mechanics in mechanically ventilated patients. Respir Care. 2014;59(11):1773-94.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"237","text":"4. Lucangelo U, Bernabé F, Blanch L. Lung mechanics at the bedside: make it simple. Curr Opin Crit Care. 2007;13(1):64-72.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"237","text":"5. Mittman C, et al. Relationship between chest wall and pulmonary compliance with age. J Appl Physiol. 1965;20:1211-16.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"237","text":"6. Kronenberg RS, Drage CW. Attenuation of ventilatory and heart rate responses to hypoxia and hypercapnia with aging. J Clin Invest. 1973;52:1912-19.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"237","text":"7. Tenney SM, Miller RM. Dead space ventilation in old age. J Appl Physiol. 1956;9(3):321-27.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"237","text":"8. Gattinoni L, et al. The future of mechanical ventilation: lessons from the present and the past. Crit Care. 2017;21(1):183.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"237","text":"9. Pidaparti R, et al. Aging effects on airflow dynamics and lung function in human bronchioles. PLoS One. 2017;12(8):e0183654.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"247","parent":"237","text":"10. Henderson WR, et al. Bedside ventilatory settings guided by respiratory mechanics in ARDS. Crit Care. 2025;29:234.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"248","parent":"237","text":"11. Sahetya SK, et al. Respiratory Mechanics. Anesthesiol Clin. 2021;39(3):539-53.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"249","parent":"237","text":"12. Polkey MI, et al. Contractile properties of the elderly human diaphragm. Am J Respir Crit Care Med. 1997;155(5):1560-64.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":249,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"Mod0 Fundamentos Fisiologicos iPad","id":"map_817","resolved_references":[]}